    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks for reporting @tristanbes. If you are not using Server side rendering, it's best to not include the library, or alias it to an empty module (especially for client-side).\r\n\r\nWe do a conditional `require` in a try-catch in a code path which normally only runs on the server, however depending on the way you are importing you might get a false positive for this unused code. Do you have a GitHub reproduction for it? ",
